#. <section class="sutta" id="mn111"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn111:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 111"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 111"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn111:0.2"
msgid "Anupadasutta"
msgstr "One by One"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.25"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn111:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn111:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "mn111:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn111:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn111:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn111:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn111:2.1"
msgid "“Paṇḍito, bhikkhave, sāriputto;"
msgstr "“Sāriputta is astute, mendicants."

msgctxt "mn111:2.2"
msgid "mahāpañño, bhikkhave, sāriputto;"
msgstr "He has great wisdom,"

msgctxt "mn111:2.3"
msgid "puthupañño, bhikkhave, sāriputto;"
msgstr "widespread wisdom,"

#. VAR: hāsapañño → hāsupañño (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn111:2.4"
msgid "hāsapañño, bhikkhave, sāriputto;"
msgstr "laughing wisdom,"

msgctxt "mn111:2.5"
msgid "javanapañño, bhikkhave, sāriputto;"
msgstr "swift wisdom,"

msgctxt "mn111:2.6"
msgid "tikkhapañño, bhikkhave, sāriputto;"
msgstr "sharp wisdom,"

msgctxt "mn111:2.7"
msgid "nibbedhikapañño, bhikkhave, sāriputto;"
msgstr "and penetrating wisdom."

msgctxt "mn111:2.8"
msgid "sāriputto, bhikkhave, aḍḍhamāsaṃ anupadadhammavipassanaṃ vipassati."
msgstr "For a fortnight he practiced discernment of phenomena one by one."

msgctxt "mn111:2.9"
msgid "Tatridaṃ, bhikkhave, sāriputtassa anupadadhammavipassanāya hoti."
msgstr "And this is how he did it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn111:3.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, sāriputto vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi "
"savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, "
"he entered and remained in the first absorption, which has the rapture and "
"bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected."

# In Kd 13, vavatthita is opposite to sambhinna = mixed, so = distinguished
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. VAR: paṭhame jhāne → paṭhamajjhāne (si, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn111:4.1"
msgid ""
"Ye ca paṭhame jhāne dhammā vitakko ca vicāro ca pīti ca sukhañca "
"cittekaggatā ca, phasso vedanā saññā cetanā cittaṃ chando adhimokkho vīriyaṃ "
"sati upekkhā manasikāro—tyāssa dhammā anupadavavatthitā honti."
msgstr ""
"And he distinguished the phenomena in the first absorption one by one: "
"placing and keeping and rapture and bliss and unification of mind; contact, "
"feeling, perception, intention, mind, enthusiasm, decision, energy, "
"mindfulness, equanimity, and attention."

msgctxt "mn111:4.2"
msgid ""
"Tyāssa dhammā viditā uppajjanti, viditā upaṭṭhahanti, viditā abbhatthaṃ "
"gacchanti."
msgstr ""
"He knew those phenomena as they arose, as they remained, and as they went "
"away."

msgctxt "mn111:4.3"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr "He understood:"

msgctxt "mn111:4.4"
msgid "‘evaṃ kirame dhammā ahutvā sambhonti, hutvā paṭiventī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘So it seems that these phenomena, not having been, come to be; and having "
"come to be, they flit away.’"

#. VAR: appaṭibaddho → apaṭibaddho (pts1) | appaṭibandho (mr)
msgctxt "mn111:4.5"
msgid ""
"So tesu dhammesu anupāyo anapāyo anissito appaṭibaddho vippamutto visaṃyutto "
"vimariyādīkatena cetasā viharati."
msgstr ""
"And he meditated without attraction or repulsion for those phenomena; "
"independent, untied, liberated, detached, his mind free of limits."

msgctxt "mn111:4.6"
msgid "So ‘atthi uttari nissaraṇan’ti pajānāti."
msgstr "He understood: ‘There is an escape beyond.’"

msgctxt "mn111:4.7"
msgid "Tabbahulīkārā atthitvevassa hoti. (1)"
msgstr "And by repeated practice he knew for sure that there is."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.26"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn111:5.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sāriputto vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ "
"sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ "
"dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected were "
"stilled, he entered and remained in the second absorption, which has the "
"rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, "
"and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
msgctxt "mn111:6.1"
msgid ""
"Ye ca dutiye jhāne dhammā—ajjhattaṃ sampasādo ca pīti ca sukhañca "
"cittekaggatā ca, phasso vedanā saññā cetanā cittaṃ chando adhimokkho vīriyaṃ "
"sati upekkhā manasikāro—tyāssa dhammā anupadavavatthitā honti."
msgstr ""
"And he distinguished the phenomena in the second absorption one by one: "
"internal confidence and rapture and bliss and unification of mind; contact, "
"feeling, perception, intention, mind, enthusiasm, decision, energy, "
"mindfulness, equanimity, and attention."

msgctxt "mn111:6.2"
msgid ""
"Tyāssa dhammā viditā uppajjanti, viditā upaṭṭhahanti, viditā abbhatthaṃ "
"gacchanti."
msgstr ""
"He knew those phenomena as they arose, as they remained, and as they went "
"away."

msgctxt "mn111:6.3"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr "He understood:"

msgctxt "mn111:6.4"
msgid "‘evaṃ kirame dhammā ahutvā sambhonti, hutvā paṭiventī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘So it seems that these phenomena, not having been, come to be; and having "
