msgctxt "mn111:6.5"
msgid ""
"So tesu dhammesu anupāyo anapāyo anissito appaṭibaddho vippamutto visaṃyutto "
"vimariyādīkatena cetasā viharati."
msgstr ""
"And he meditated without attraction or repulsion for those phenomena; "
"independent, untied, liberated, detached, his mind free of limits."

msgctxt "mn111:6.6"
msgid "So ‘atthi uttari nissaraṇan’ti pajānāti."
msgstr "He understood: ‘There is an escape beyond.’"

msgctxt "mn111:6.7"
msgid "Tabbahulīkārā atthitvevassa hoti. (2)"
msgstr "And by repeated practice he knew for sure that there is."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn111:7.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sāriputto pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati "
"sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti. Yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘"
"upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, he entered and remained in the "
"third absorption, where he meditated with equanimity, mindful and aware, "
"personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘"
"Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
msgctxt "mn111:8.1"
msgid ""
"Ye ca tatiye jhāne dhammā—sukhañca sati ca sampajaññañca cittekaggatā ca, "
"phasso vedanā saññā cetanā cittaṃ chando adhimokkho vīriyaṃ sati upekkhā "
"manasikāro—"
msgstr ""
"And he distinguished the phenomena in the third absorption one by one: bliss "
"and mindfulness and awareness and unification of mind; contact, feeling, "
"perception, intention, mind, enthusiasm, decision, energy, mindfulness, "
"equanimity, and attention."

msgctxt "mn111:8.2"
msgid ""
"tyāssa dhammā anupadavavatthitā honti, tyāssa dhammā viditā uppajjanti, "
"viditā upaṭṭhahanti, viditā abbhatthaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr ""
"He knew those phenomena as they arose, as they remained, and as they went "
"away."

msgctxt "mn111:8.3"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr "He understood:"

msgctxt "mn111:8.4"
msgid "‘evaṃ kirame dhammā ahutvā sambhonti, hutvā paṭiventī’ti."
msgstr ""
