msgctxt "mn111:8.5"
msgid ""
"So tesu dhammesu anupāyo anapāyo anissito appaṭibaddho vippamutto visaṃyutto "
"vimariyādīkatena cetasā viharati."
msgstr ""
"And he meditated without attraction or repulsion for those phenomena; "
"independent, untied, liberated, detached, his mind free of limits."

msgctxt "mn111:8.6"
msgid "So ‘atthi uttari nissaraṇan’ti pajānāti."
msgstr "He understood: ‘There is an escape beyond.’"

msgctxt "mn111:8.7"
msgid "Tabbahulīkārā atthitvevassa hoti. (3)"
msgstr "And by repeated practice he knew for sure that there is."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.27"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn111:9.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sāriputto sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā "
"pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ "
"upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, with the giving up of pleasure and pain, and the ending of "
"former happiness and sadness, he entered and remained in the fourth "
"absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
msgctxt "mn111:10.1"
msgid ""
"Ye ca catutthe jhāne dhammā—upekkhā adukkhamasukhā vedanā passaddhattā "
"cetaso anābhogo satipārisuddhi cittekaggatā ca, phasso vedanā saññā cetanā "
"cittaṃ chando adhimokkho vīriyaṃ sati upekkhā manasikāro—tyāssa dhammā "
"anupadavavatthitā honti."
msgstr ""
"And he distinguished the phenomena in the fourth absorption one by one: "
"equanimity and neutral feeling and mental unconcern due to tranquility and "
"pure mindfulness and unification of mind; contact, feeling, perception, "
"intention, mind, enthusiasm, decision, energy, mindfulness, equanimity, and "
"attention."

msgctxt "mn111:10.2"
msgid ""
"Tyāssa dhammā viditā uppajjanti, viditā upaṭṭhahanti, viditā abbhatthaṃ "
"gacchanti."
msgstr ""
